# test-send.http — manual tests for the SMS reminder function
#
# Use with the VS Code "REST Client" extension: click "Send Request" above each request.
# Or adapt the curl / PowerShell commands at the bottom.
#
# NOTES:
#  - Replace the placeholder "to" number with a REAL number you control before testing.
#  - Do NOT commit a real phone number (this repo is public) — keep the placeholder in git.
#  - SMS will only actually deliver once the Twilio A2P 10DLC campaign is APPROVED.
#    Before approval, expect carrier filtering or an error response.

@baseUrl = https://papi-sundaygap.netlify.app

### 1) Sanity check — is the function deployed and reachable?
# Expected: HTTP 405 "Method Not Allowed" (the function only accepts POST).
GET {{baseUrl}}/.netlify/functions/send-sms

### 2) Send a real test reminder.
# Expected on success: HTTP 200  -> { "success": true, "sid": "SM..." }
# Expected on failure: HTTP 400/500 -> { "error": "..." }
POST {{baseUrl}}/.netlify/functions/send-sms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "+15555550100",
  "message": "Test: Papi Sunday-Gap care reminder system is working."
}
